-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription + event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM raw_billing_events
)
SELECT
    event_id,
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_user_companies.sql
```sql
-- Enrich users with company information, handle nullable company_id
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        u.user_id,
        u.name AS user_name,
        u.email,
        u.company_id
    FROM raw_users u
)
SELECT
    source.user_id,
    source.user_name,
    source.email,
    COALESCE(c.company_id, 0) AS company_id,
    COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS company_name,
    COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
FROM source
LEFT JOIN raw_companies c
    ON c.company_id = source.company_id
```

-- int_subscription_plans.sql
```sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with plan tier information, handle missing plan_ids
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status
    FROM raw_subscriptions s
)
SELECT
    source.subscription_id,
    source.user_id,
    COALESCE(p.plan_id, 0) AS plan_id,
    COALESCE(p.name, '(unknown)') AS plan_name,
    COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
    COALESCE(p.monthly_price, 0.00) AS monthly_price
FROM source
LEFT JOIN raw_plans p
    ON p.plan_id = source.plan_id
```

```sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH user_companies AS (
    SELECT
        user_id,
        industry
    FROM int_user_companies
),
deduped_billing AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        SUM(amount) AS total_amount
    FROM stg_billing_events
    GROUP BY subscription_id, event_month
),
enriched_subscriptions AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.tier,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        s.monthly_price
    FROM int_subscription_plans s
)
SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month) AS month,
    e.tier,
    uc.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(b.total_amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT s.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM deduped_billing b
LEFT JOIN enriched_subscriptions s
    ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
LEFT JOIN user_companies uc
    ON uc.user_id = s.user_id
WHERE s.status = 'active'
    AND (s.started_at IS NULL OR s.started_at <= b.event_month)
    AND (s.ended_at IS NULL OR s.ended_at >= b.event_month)
GROUP BY
    DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month),
    e.tier,
    uc.industry
ORDER BY month DESC, e.tier, uc.industry
